function keep_only_names(words::Vector{String})
    return filter(word -> word[1] == uppercasefirst(word[1]), words)
end
```

This function uses the `filter` built-in function to iteratively check each word in the list and keep only those where the first letter is equal to the uppercased version of that same letter. The `uppercasefirst` function is used to convert the first letter to uppercase without affecting the rest of the string.
